TY  - JOUR
TI  - NONPARAMETRIC ANALYSIS OF RANDOM UTILITY MODELS
AU  - Smeulders, Bart
AU  - Cherchye, Laurens
AU  - De Rock, Bram
AB  - [Kitamura and Stoye (2018) recently proposed a nonparametric statistical test for random utility models of consumer behavior. The test is formulated in terms of linear inequality constraints and a quadratic objective function. While the nonparametric test is conceptually appealing, its practical implementation is computationally challenging. In this paper, we develop a column generation approach to operationalize the test. These novel computational tools generate considerable computational gains in practice, which substantially increases the empirical usefulness of Kitamura and Stoye’s statistical test.]
